How to Run Your Session Effectively According to Google AI

1. Keep DeepSeek V4 Flash as your baselineKeep opencode-go/deepseek-v4-flash active for 80% of your session. It costs next to nothing against your 5-hour window limit, features a massive 1.0M context window, and functions with incredibly low latency.

2. Swap to MiniMax M3 for active feature implementationWhen you need to write full logic modules or generate continuous tests, toggle over to opencode-go/minimax-m3. It punches way above its price class—frequently nearing frontier model benchmarks on SWE-bench—while remaining incredibly budget-friendly.

3. Reserve Qwen3.7 Max or GLM-5.2 strictly for blockagesOnly switch your target configuration to opencode-go/qwen3.7-max or opencode-go/glm-5.2 when you hit a wall. These models possess elite intelligence profiles but have high per-token pricing that can rapidly chip away at your rolling caps.
